play: `\\"SIMULATION PASSED\\"`.\\n    *   When the *first* mismatch occurs, display inputs, DUT outputs, and expected outputs at that time.\\n*   **Display Logic Refinement:** The original TB used `stats1.first_mismatch_time` and `stats1.first_error_type` (though inconsistently updated in the provided previous_tb). I will streamline the logic to capture the *first* time *any* mismatch occurs (either general or Z mismatch) and use that time for the failure message, while still tracking individual errors.\\n*   **Signal Display:** The requirement asks to display signals in HEX/BIN format if width <= 64. I will implement a helper task for this, similar to the attempt in the previous_tb, but ensure it is used upon the *first* mismatch.\\n*   **Correction/Fixes from Log:** The failure log indicates severe syntax errors related to struct usage (`Error in struct/union member`). This often happens when mixing Verilog-2001 style struct definitions with SystemVerilog features or using incorrect syntax for structure field access. I will ensure strict SystemVerilog syntax for the `struct` definition and member access (`stats1.errors`, etc.). I will also correct the small typos observed in the previous TB (e.g., `sstats1` instead of `stats1`).\\n*   **Implementing First Mismatch Display:** I will track the time of the first general mismatch (`stats1.first_mismatch_time`) and the time of the first Z mismatch (`stats1.errortime_z`). The final failure message must refer to the earliest of these two times if both occurred.\\n*   **Final Display Logic:** The final display must use `stats1.errors` (general mismatch count) for the failure message count, as per the requirement: `"  \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n 